data.title: Pulse Music Board
data.meta_description: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rd-Ymlhhc7k  Signed to a major label and produced by Missy and Timbaland
data.text:
Post by tamed09 on

www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rd-Ymlhhc7k

Signed to a major label and produced by Missy and Timbaland

Post by Deleted on

Looooooong overdue. One of my favorite R&B voices of the past 15 years. It's heavenly.

Her second album wasn't as good as her debut, but I still enjoyed a lot of songs on it.

I could see her having a mini-comeback like Keke Wyatt with the right material.

Post by Deleted on

Exciting. I didn't really like her second album, but I loved her first.

I've been listening to Proceed regularly since she leaked that.

Post by Linnethia Monique on

Hopefully this actually materializes. I give her 2nd album a pass because I love Turn Da Lights Off and it brought me one of my favorite Tweet jams, Cab Ride.

Post by Deleted on

My favorites on It's Me Again were "Small Change" and "I'm Done".

Post by tamed09 on

Shook Up ft Free should have made the album...I loved thats song

Post by Active Aggressive on

The only thing I remember from her sophomore album were Turn Da Lights Off (a song that my MOM told me about, LOL. I had completely forgotten about Tweet after her debut), Cab Ride (that sample...), and the ultimate jam Sports, Sex, and Food. That New Orleans flavor...

Either way, I am excited for her comeback because I really enjoy her voice and style.

Post by wavey.✨️ on

"Call Me" & "Turn Da Lights Off" are my favorite tracks from her.

Post by Heart Shaped Box on

"You" is my jam. I stan for this girl so hard. She is deserving of more fame.

Post by SHOOTER on

Her first album is a classic but the second album was a solid B effort. Iceberg, You, Cab Ride, Small Change, Steer and I'm Done are still in regular rotation with me.

Post by Active Aggressive on

"Call Me" & "Turn Da Lights Off" are my favorite tracks from her.

C-c-c-c-c-CALL ME at the break of dawn. I'll be sure to meet you with no pannies on. My mom loved that one too. Shake it shake it shake it BOUNCE. I was a sucker for those Middle Eastern-sounding beats.

Post by SHOOTER on

She still resents Call Me but it will forever be one of the best booty call jams of the '00s!

On another note, somebody needs to unearth the Smoking Cigarettes video and upload it to YT.

Post by Caviar on

"I'm Done" is like one of her best songs ever because the lyrics are so real. It's weird because it feels so out of place on It's Me Again when it should have been on "Southern Hummingbird". It's so good she left DuBose Music Group and I'm curious who she went with.

Here's a few of my other fav Tweet songs:

"Oops"

"C 4Eva" - Maxwell raved about it that summer.

"Always Will"

"Beautiful"

"Cab Ride"

"Love Again"

Post by Ling-Ling on

WHAT!!!!! This is so exciting. Her voice is just... butter. One of my favorite recent R&B voices.

Her first album had so many killer tracks. But her second album... so bad. Although "Turn Da Lights Off" will forever be a jam.

Definitely looking forward to this, although I'm slightly skeptical about Tim & Missy.

Post by Deleted on

I know Timbaland's sound isn't everyone's cup of tea these days but has Missy ever gone wrong writing for an R&B singer that can really SANG? Besides I Deserve It that is.

Post by Ling-Ling on

Missy has a good record with female singers, I will admit. Hell, I even like "I Deserve It," haha. She just hasn't produced a lot of work lately, so I'm wondering what she's going to bring. I mean she can barely even get her own music career together.

Post by bat1990 on

I'll believe it when I see it...I've been let down too many times in the past 10 years since It's Me Again.

Post by SHOOTER on

I'll believe it when I see it...I've been let down too many times in the past 10 years since It's Me Again.

I've got confirmation her deal is signed. She left DuBose specifically because they couldn't pull it together to properly release her music (despite DuBose starting the music division of his company specifically for her).

Post by Ginger Spice on

Exciting! I enjoy both of her albums. "Smoking Cigarettes" is my all-time favorite song by her.

I like "Turn Da Lights Off", but I would like it a lot more if Missy didn't take up half of the track with her ad-libs. I had a similar problem with a lot of Missy's productions for Monica.

Post by SHOOTER on

Why does she resent "call me"?

She more so resents the fact that Elektra pushed it as the second single over Smoking Cigarettes because she felt it pigeonholed her and her sound and the general public never moved beyond that perception of her.

Post by bat1990 on

Exciting! I enjoy both of her albums. "Smoking Cigarettes" is my all-time favorite song by her.

I like "Turn Da Lights Off", but I would like it a lot more if Missy didn't take up half of the track with her ad-libs. I had a similar problem with a lot of Missy's productions for Monica.

If Aaliyah were still alive, she probably would've said "Missy! Stop grunting all over these tracks! That's not going on my album"

Post by Queen of Insomnia. on

My favorites get signed by major labels in 2010s. First Tamia, now Tweet. YAY. I didn't see that coming. I just wanna celebrate.

Post by Active Aggressive on

about Aaliyah. Yeah, I have never been a fan of Missy's mannish, guttural grunts on these otherwise great R&B songs either. I actually went back and listened to all of Tweet's second album and in parts it's even stronger than her debut. Can't wait!

Post by Heart Shaped Box on

Missy does suffer from Jermaine Dupri syndrome, but, she's never done any harm to Tweet's music. Their chemistry is on point. Let me also throw my love for Thugman in this mix. That song is a jam and a half, and Missy even delivers a solid cameo.

Post by steevy on

2016?

january 2016?

why so far away?
